			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, if the NMI suspends the IRQ until it's over, if your NMI routine is a consistent length, and if you can get the DPCM to trigger its IRQ anywhere in the middle of it (seems like a nice wide target), it'll automatically get synched with the end of the NMI every frame. You should be able to get two updates per frame in very reliably (though one of the updates might be slightly longer; probably this is fine).
<br />
<br />Might take a little care to get the first frame's IRQ aligned properly, but once you catch the first DPCM IRQ in your NMI it should be stable afterward.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

